Constructor Detail

Entity

public Entity(String nick,
              String ident,
              String host,
              SocketAddress address)

Constructs an entity with the specified IRC nick, ident string, host, and address.

Here the address effectively refers to the network. Note that this distinction may be too strict sometimes: networks often have multiple servers and even multiple ports on the same server; therefore if you're connected to a network multiple times you might get objects which really represent the same entity but have different addresses. The equalsIgnoreAddress(Entity) method is provided to allow checking for equality in such cases.

Parameters:
nick - the IRC nick, or null if one isn't known (as in the case of a server)
ident - the ident, or null if one isn't known (as in the case of a server)
host - the entity's host
address - the address with which this entity is associated

isUser

public boolean isUser()

Checks whether or not this entity represents an IRC user. If it's not a user, then it's probably a server.

A user is defined as an entity that has both a nick and an ident.

Returns:
true if and only if this entity represents an IRC user

equalsIgnoreAddress

public boolean equalsIgnoreAddress(Entity e)
Indicates whether some other entity is "equal to" this one, ignoring the address. This might come in handy for comparing entities from connections to different servers or different ports of the same network.

Parameters:
e - the entity with which to compare
Returns:
true if this entity is the same as the argument, false otherwise
